text.tspan: Share of workers in informal employment: agriculture vs.
Share of employed people working in jobs that lack basic social or legal protection and employment benefits. Does not
include illegal and illicit activities. The agricultural sector includes agriculture, forestry, and fishing.
Share of workers in informal employment in the non-agricultural sector
Share of workers in informal employment in the agricultural sector

Note: Figures refer to
national estimates
and may not be fully comparable across countries. Employment is defined in line with the 13th ICLS
and includes the production of goods for own use, such as subsistence farming.
